text: The Sealand National Sports Association (SNSA) is the official governing body for sports activities in the Principality of Sealand, a self-declared micronation located on a former World War II sea fort in the North Sea. Established to promote and manage sports within Sealand, the SNSA organizes various events and competitions, aiming to foster a sense of community and national pride among its citizens and supporters. == Coaches == Manager Nat Span G W D L GF GA Win % Honours Christian Olsen 2003–2006 1 0 1 0 2 2 0% Neil Forsyth 2009–2013 3 1 1 1 4 5 33.33% Julian Dicks 2013 3 1 0 2 5 14 33.33% Ed Stubbs 2013–present 7 5 2 0 24 10 71.43% ==References== Category:Principality of Sealand Category:2004 establishments in Europe
